This paper is primarily focused on malware classification, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques, specifically random forests, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of graphs and Markov chains, which are commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves vectorization techniques, which are often used in data science (cs.DS).
